\pmod {2 \pi i}
\cos(2kx) = \dfrac{e^{ikx} + e^{-ikx}}2
\sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{\cos(2kx)}k = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{e^{i2kx} + e^{-i2kx}}{2k} = \dfrac12 \left(-\log \left(1-e^{i2x} \right)-\log \left(1-e^{-i2x} \right) \right) = - \dfrac12 \log \left(2 - 2\cos(2x) \right) = - \dfrac12 \log(4 \sin^2(x)) = - \log 2 - \log(\sin(x))
-\log(\sin(x)) = \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \dfrac{\cos(2kx)}k + \log 2
